5:
...And that's how the impatient Santa
got all the monsters together and
started Halloween.
9:
Hmm, say, Hans. You don't like Santa
much, do ya?
12:
Why would I? The whole story's a big
lie anyway.
14: A lie? Now why do you think that?
17:
If he really existed, then there
wouldn't be kids like me...
20:
Hans is pretty new to the
orphanage. He still hasn't adjusted
to life here yet...
24:
Say, Lilie... How about this Santa
fella... Is he real?
28:
U-uh... You want to know if Santa
exists? I mean, I think there was a
real person who he was based off,
but...
31:
Historical interpretations on the
matter are... complicated, to say the
least.
35:
Complicated, you say! 
Now that's a word I like to hear.
41:
Ah-HAH! Now THAT'S a spectacular
entrance, wouldn't you say, Alk?
46:
Are you CRAZY?! We can't just go
and—
50:
Oh my, you're all hands today—
a rambunctious one, aren't ya!
54:
You're one to talk! What ever
happened to just giving out
presents?!
57:
I've been doing that! But that's
beside the point—we're here to pull
off a great heist! I'm going to steal 
a certain well-hidden holy book!
60:
You're free to join me—if you don't
mind spending the night all alone
together, of course!
62:
Thieves! After them! 
Don't let them get away!
65:
Well look at that! If they catch us,
we'll be branded as thieves for the
rest of our lives. How exciting!
76:
Should... I even ask where you got
that book from?
82:
...Probably not. I'm so sorry, I promise
I'll find a way to get this back to
where it belongs! No matter what.
86:
Oh-hoh, I'm just happy I got to see
Alk let out his cunning side! I LIKE it!
89:
And what's more is, we found out
more about the "original" Santa! 
To think he was a legendary figure 
who led humans all the way to the
Farlands!
91:
Meaning, there really DID exist a
saint who wanted to bring
happiness to children! We'll have to
let Hans know that part wasn't a lie.
95:
I honestly don't even know where to
begin with this whole fiasco.
99:
But, as for Hans... I don't know if
hearing about Santa will be of much
help to him. He has other issues to
face.
107:
So you've already realized? Unlike
the other kids at the orphanage, 
it's not Santa he's waiting for. 
It's his parents.
111:
The truth is his parents aren't dead.
But, they're also not coming back to
see him. Truth or lie, his pain
remains the same.
114:
No matter. 
This was all purely to
sate my own curiosity.
123:
I'm sorry, buddy, but I'm not your
father!
126:
I'm Folus! A fiend from a faraway
place where the sky has no stars!
129:
Oh, and I'm also Santa's little helper
this year! Happy Holidays!
132:
You're that clown girl from earlier...
Wait, you're not... human?
135:
Ding-ding-ding! You've got it—
I know we must be pretty scary to
you, huh?
138:
But don't you worry! First and
foremost, I'm Santa's helper!
141:
Actually, I got captured by Santa,
you see. Lost to him in a fight! So,
now I have to work for him to get my
freedom back.
144:
So, as part of my job, I'm here to give
blessings out to kids. Just like you,
Hans.
147:
So, Santa is real after all? Then what
about my dad, could—
150:
I'm sorry, Hans. There's nothing I can
do about that.
153:
Santa and his helpers aren't gods,
after all! All we can do is bring a
liiiittle bit of happiness to people,
from time to time.
157:
But we are watching you. And we do
love you.
170:
Ah-HAH! Say what you will about the
educational value of what I just did, 
I still think that was one of my finer
performances!
174:
But hey, maybe he'll think it was all a
dream! I bet it'll make for a nice
memory when he grows up.
179:
I... admit I'm a bit surprised at how
you went about it, but... thank you
for helping out, Folus.
186:
It's just... I heard from Alk that you
didn't like telling lies.
190: Was it, though? A lie, I mean.
197: I mean... Santa is you guys, right?
200:
The legend continues to this very
day because of people like you.
Through pure will, you kept it alive.
202:
All I did was help out a little! That
doesn't strike me as a lie!
209:
It's the honest to goodness truth,
and I'll hear no ifs, ands, or buts!
Anyway, I'm off, see ya!
213:
It's starting to snow. I wonder if it'll
pile up this time?
218:
I tell ya, what's the point in having
lies? Why not just take those lies...
and turn them into truths!
221:
Ah, never mind! Anyway, it's looking
chilly tonight... The perfect weather
for a snuggle together, with you!
Dontcha think?
224:
Or—here's an idea—we could not,
and you could cut it out with the
inappropriate advances.
228:
Fiiine. I guess I'll just have to settle
for being friends.
...For now.
